---
import SiteLayout from "../../../layouts/SiteLayout.astro";

const schema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "Article",
  "headline": "Interactive Relationship Health Assessment",
  "description": "Evaluate the health of your relationship based on communication, trust, and boundaries with our anonymous self-assessment tool.",
  "author": {
    "@type": "Organization",
    "name": "The Nookie Nook"
  },
  "mainEntity": {
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What are the signs of a healthy relationship?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Healthy relationships are built on mutual respect, trust, open communication, shared boundaries, and a foundation of equality."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Can a relationship survive a lack of physical intimacy?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Yes, but it requires open communication. Physical intimacy needs vary greatly. As long as both partners are communicating honestly and finding other ways to connect, a relationship can thrive."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Is this assessment a diagnostic tool?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "No. This tool is purely educational and designed to prompt self-reflection and communication with your partner. It is not a substitute for professional couples counseling."
        }
      }
    ]
  }
};
---
<SiteLayout
  site="nookienook"
  title="Relationship Health Assessment Tool | The Nookie Nook"
  description="Evaluate your relationship's communication, trust, and intimacy with our interactive self-assessment. Gain insights and actionable tips."
  canonical="https://thenookienook.com/relationship-health-check"
  schema={schema}
>
  <div class="page-content">
    <div class="hero">
      <h1>Relationship Health Assessment</h1>
      <p>A tool for self-reflection, designed to help you communicate better.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="content-section">
      <div class="warning-banner">
        <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This assessment is for educational purposes only. It is completely anonymous—we do not store your answers. This is not a diagnostic tool and cannot replace the advice of a licensed therapist or counselor.
      </div>

      <p>Part of our <a href="/sites/nookienook/sexual-health-guide">Comprehensive Sexual Health Guide</a> series.</p>

      <p>Every relationship has ups and downs, but foundational markers like trust, mutual respect, and safe communication should remain consistent. This 15-question assessment evaluates your current dynamic across three key areas: Communication & Conflict, Boundaries & Respect, and Intimacy & Connection.</p>

      <div class="assessment-container" id="app-container">

        <div id="intro-screen" class="screen active">
          <h2>Ready to reflect?</h2>
          <p>Read each statement and select how frequently it applies to your current relationship. Answer honestly; there are no right or wrong answers, only opportunities for growth.</p>
          <button class="primary-btn mt-2" onclick="startAssessment()">Start Assessment</button>
        </div>

        <div id="question-screen" class="screen">
          <div class="progress-bar">
            <div id="progress-fill" class="progress-fill"></div>
          </div>
          <div class="question-header">
            <span id="category-badge" class="category-badge">Category</span>
            <span class="question-counter"><span id="q-current">1</span>/15</span>
          </div>

          <h3 id="question-text" class="question-text">Question text goes here?</h3>

          <div class="options-grid">
            <button class="option-btn" onclick="answerQuestion(1)">Rarely / Never (1)</button>
            <button class="option-btn" onclick="answerQuestion(2)">Occasionally (2)</button>
            <button class="option-btn" onclick="answerQuestion(3)">Sometimes (3)</button>
            <button class="option-btn" onclick="answerQuestion(4)">Often (4)</button>
            <button class="option-btn" onclick="answerQuestion(5)">Almost Always (5)</button>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div id="results-screen" class="screen">
          <h2>Your Assessment Results</h2>
          <p>Based on your answers, here is a breakdown of your relationship dynamics in key areas.</p>

          <div class="score-summary">
            <div class="total-score-box">
              <div class="score-label">Overall Health Score</div>
              <div class="score-value"><span id="total-score">0</span> / 75</div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="category-results">
            <div class="category-card">
              <h4>Communication & Conflict</h4>
              <div class="cat-score">Score: <span id="score-comm">0</span> / 25</div>
              <p id="feedback-comm" class="feedback-text"></p>
            </div>

            <div class="category-card">
              <h4>Boundaries & Respect</h4>
              <div class="cat-score">Score: <span id="score-bound">0</span> / 25</div>
              <p id="feedback-bound" class="feedback-text"></p>
            </div>

            <div class="category-card">
              <h4>Intimacy & Connection</h4>
              <div class="cat-score">Score: <span id="score-int">0</span> / 25</div>
              <p id="feedback-int" class="feedback-text"></p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="results-action">
            <p><strong>Next Steps:</strong> The most valuable part of this tool is what you do next. Consider sharing these results with your partner to start a dialogue. If you scored low in multiple areas and feel unsafe, please seek help immediately.</p>
            <button class="primary-btn" onclick="location.reload()">Take Assessment Again</button>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>

      <h2>What Makes a Healthy Relationship?</h2>
      <p>Healthy relationships don't just happen; they are built intentionally. While no relationship is perfect, secure partnerships generally share these traits:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Open Communication:</strong> You can discuss difficult topics without fear of explosive anger or being stonewalled.</li>
        <li><strong>Respected Boundaries:</strong> When you say "no" or ask for space, your partner respects it without guilt-tripping you. Learn more in our <a href="/sites/nookienook/consent-communication-guide">Consent & Communication Guide</a>.</li>
        <li><strong>Mutual Independence:</strong> You both maintain friendships, hobbies, and an identity outside of the relationship.</li>
        <li><strong>Equality:</strong> Decisions are made together, and labor (both physical and emotional) is shared fairly.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <script is:inline>
    const questions = [
      // Communication & Conflict (Items 0-4)
      { id: 1, text: "When we disagree, we listen to each other's perspectives without interrupting or resorting to name-calling.", category: "comm" },
      { id: 2, text: "I feel comfortable bringing up difficult or sensitive topics with my partner.", category: "comm" },
      { id: 3, text: "After an argument, we are able to repair the connection, apologize, and move forward.", category: "comm" },
      { id: 4, text: "My partner takes my feelings seriously, rather than dismissing them as 'too sensitive' or 'crazy'.", category: "comm" },
      { id: 5, text: "We discuss our expectations regarding finances, household chores, and future goals openly.", category: "comm" },

      // Boundaries & Respect (Items 5-9)
      { id: 6, text: "If I tell my partner I need space or alone time, they respect it without making me feel guilty.", category: "bound" },
      { id: 7, text: "I never feel pressured, coerced, or manipulated into doing sexual activities I don't want to do.", category: "bound" },
      { id: 8, text: "My partner respects my privacy (e.g., they don't demand to look through my phone or emails).", category: "bound" },
      { id: 9, text: "We support each other's friendships and hobbies outside of the relationship.", category: "bound" },
      { id: 10, text: "I feel safe expressing a differing opinion from my partner without fear of retaliation.", category: "bound" },

      // Intimacy & Connection (Items 10-14)
      { id: 11, text: "We intentionally make time to connect emotionally, beyond just discussing logistics and chores.", category: "int" },
      { id: 12, text: "I feel desired and appreciated by my partner.", category: "int" },
      { id: 13, text: "We can openly discuss our sexual needs, desires, and boundaries.", category: "int" },
      { id: 14, text: "I trust my partner completely to be faithful to the agreements of our relationship structure.", category: "int" },
      { id: 15, text: "We show physical affection in non-sexual ways (e.g., hugging, holding hands, cuddling).", category: "int" }
    ];

    let currentQ = 0;
    let scores = { comm: 0, bound: 0, int: 0 };

    function startAssessment() {
      document.getElementById('intro-screen').classList.remove('active');
      document.getElementById('question-screen').classList.add('active');
      renderQuestion();
    }

    function renderQuestion() {
      const q = questions[currentQ];
      document.getElementById('q-current').innerText = currentQ + 1;
      document.getElementById('question-text').innerText = q.text;

      let catName = "";
      if (q.category === 'comm') catName = "Communication & Conflict";
      if (q.category === 'bound') catName = "Boundaries & Respect";
      if (q.category === 'int') catName = "Intimacy & Connection";

      document.getElementById('category-badge').innerText = catName;

      const progressPercent = ((currentQ) / questions.length) * 100;
      document.getElementById('progress-fill').style.width = `${progressPercent}%`;
    }

    function answerQuestion(value) {
      const category = questions[currentQ].category;
      scores[category] += value;

      currentQ++;

      if (currentQ < questions.length) {
        renderQuestion();
      } else {
        showResults();
      }
    }

    function getFeedbackText(score, category) {
      if (score >= 20) return "Excellent. You exhibit strong, healthy patterns in this area. Continue to nurture this aspect of your relationship.";
      if (score >= 15) return "Good. There is a solid foundation, but occasionally miscommunications or misalignments happen. This is a great area for focused conversation.";
      if (score >= 10) return "Needs Attention. You may frequently experience friction, misunderstanding, or a lack of fulfillment in this area. Consider setting aside dedicated time to discuss this with your partner.";
      return "Critical Warning. A low score here indicates potential toxicity, deep disconnect, or disrespect. Please prioritize your emotional safety and consider seeking professional counseling.";
    }

    function showResults() {
      document.getElementById('question-screen').classList.remove('active');
      document.getElementById('results-screen').classList.add('active');

      const total = scores.comm + scores.bound + scores.int;

      document.getElementById('total-score').innerText = total;

      document.getElementById('score-comm').innerText = scores.comm;
      document.getElementById('feedback-comm').innerText = getFeedbackText(scores.comm, 'comm');

      document.getElementById('score-bound').innerText = scores.bound;
      document.getElementById('feedback-bound').innerText = getFeedbackText(scores.bound, 'bound');

      document.getElementById('score-int').innerText = scores.int;
      document.getElementById('feedback-int').innerText = getFeedbackText(scores.int, 'int');
    }
  </script>

  <style is:inline>
    .page-content { max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 2rem 1.5rem; }
    .hero { text-align: center; padding: 3rem 0 2rem; }
    .hero h1 { font-size: 2.2rem; font-weight: 800; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; color: var(--accent-color); }
    .hero p { color: var(--text-secondary); font-size: 1.2rem; }

    .content-section { margin-bottom: 3rem; }
    .content-section h2 { font-size: 1.8rem; margin-top: 2.5rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; color: var(--accent-color); }
    .content-section p { margin-bottom: 1.2rem; font-size: 1.1rem; line-height: 1.7; }
    .content-section a { color: var(--accent-color); text-decoration: underline; }
    .content-section a:hover { color: var(--text-primary); }
    .content-section ul { padding-left: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
    .content-section li { margin-bottom: 0.8rem; line-height: 1.6; }

    .warning-banner { background-color: rgba(224, 90, 90, 0.1); border-left: 4px solid #E05A5A; padding: 1rem 1.5rem; border-radius: 4px; margin-bottom: 2rem; color: var(--text-primary); font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.5; }

    .assessment-container { background: var(--bg-color); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); border-radius: 12px; padding: 2.5rem; margin: 2.5rem 0; box-shadow: 0 4px 6px rgba(0,0,0,0.1); min-height: 400px; }

    .screen { display: none; }
    .screen.active { display: block; animation: fadeIn 0.3s ease-in-out; }
    @keyframes fadeIn { from { opacity: 0; transform: translateY(10px); } to { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); } }

    .primary-btn { background: var(--accent-color); color: #fff; border: none; padding: 1rem 2rem; border-radius: 8px; font-size: 1.1rem; font-weight: 700; cursor: pointer; transition: opacity 0.2s; display: inline-block; }
    .primary-btn:hover { opacity: 0.9; }
    .mt-2 { margin-top: 2rem; }

    .progress-bar { width: 100%; height: 8px; background: rgba(255,255,255,0.1); border-radius: 4px; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; overflow: hidden; }
    .progress-fill { height: 100%; background: var(--accent-color); width: 0%; transition: width 0.3s ease; }

    .question-header { display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center; margin-bottom: 2rem; }
    .category-badge { background: rgba(232, 67, 147, 0.15); color: var(--accent-color); padding: 0.3rem 0.8rem; border-radius: 99px; font-size: 0.85rem; font-weight: 600; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.5px; }
    .question-counter { font-family: var(--font-mono); color: var(--text-secondary); font-size: 0.9rem; }

    .question-text { font-size: 1.6rem; color: var(--text-primary); line-height: 1.4; margin-bottom: 2.5rem; font-weight: 600; }

    .options-grid { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.8rem; }
    .option-btn { background: var(--card-bg); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-primary); padding: 1.2rem; border-radius: 8px; font-size: 1.1rem; text-align: left; cursor: pointer; transition: all 0.2s; }
    .option-btn:hover { border-color: var(--accent-color); background: rgba(232, 67, 147, 0.05); transform: translateX(5px); }

    /* Results Screen */
    .score-summary { display: flex; justify-content: center; margin: 2rem 0; }
    .total-score-box { background: var(--card-bg); border: 1px solid var(--accent-color); border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.5rem 3rem; text-align: center; }
    .score-label { color: var(--text-secondary); text-transform: uppercase; font-size: 0.9rem; letter-spacing: 1px; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
    .score-value { font-size: 2.5rem; font-weight: 800; color: var(--accent-color); font-family: var(--font-mono); }
    .score-value span { color: var(--text-primary); }

    .category-results { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 2.5rem; }
    .category-card { background: var(--card-bg); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); border-radius: 8px; padding: 1.5rem; }
    .category-card h4 { margin-top: 0; color: var(--accent-color); font-size: 1.2rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
    .cat-score { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 1.1rem; color: var(--text-primary); margin-bottom: 1rem; font-weight: 600; }
    .feedback-text { color: var(--text-secondary); font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.5; margin-bottom: 0; }

    .results-action { text-align: center; border-top: 1px solid var(--border-color); padding-top: 2rem; }
  </style>
</SiteLayout>
